Global investors  bought a  net 12.6
billion rupees ($235 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1.7 percent to 858.8 billion rupees, according
to the exchangeâ€™s  website . Open interest reached a record 1.6
trillion rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 3.35 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
